element.name: Woodside by moyle, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)
element.description: This is a small cache that is starting off with a few little goodies in it. I'm not sure how accurate the co-ordinates are because of the trees, but it shouldn't present too much trouble for the seasoned geocacher!!

ul.li:
2010-05-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by merann
Found this cache fairly quickly without having to root about on the ground. Out - Ball. In - Football keyring. TFTC, Merann.

2010-04-04T19:00:00Z : Found it by tolmaion
The search for this cache was easy - but very unpleasant. The park along the Dodder is nice alright but here, among the trees, all you get is cans and other rubbish. I am glad I had gloves with me. I would not have liked to dig around in this dirt with my bare hands. Maybe the owner should consider moving this cache to a slightly nicer location?
In: - Out: -
TFTC

2010-04-04T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by Hvva
Was given a renewed hope with the log "Spotted easily on approach", but went back and still did not see it. Maybe a GPS is required for this one?

2010-04-03T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by Hvva
Missed it this time.

2010-04-03T19:00:00Z : Found it by Toffee Man
Last find of a great days caching with Blue Jay 59. TFTC Toffee Man #286

2008-10-11T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by Kersti.com
Last time we were here there were far too many muggles hanging around. This time we headed here and no-one around. However, the tree cover was a problem and the area is quite lush at the moment so we were unsuccessful - I called it quits when I started to get creepy feelings that maybe I should have got the Hep injections when I had a chance to a few years ago after all. On to the next one.
